other_tests.findings: Fluid could not be aspirated on the initial attempt; 2 to 3 cc of sterile saline were injected and reaspirated. Core bone-biopsy specimens showed chronic granulomatous inflammation with giant cells, plasma cells, and necrotic bone. Cultures were negative for bacteria, fungi, and acid-fast bacilli.
other_tests.changes_over_time: After initial treatment with itraconazole, the patient experienced side effects and was switched to high-dose fluconazole. He chose to discontinue antifungal therapy and died after transitioning to hospice care.

other_tests.findings: Three sets of blood cultures were negative.
